Git is set up on www.oyranos.org. To use git install the git-core package.

You need currently [http://www.markus-raab.org/ftp/elektra-0.7.0.tar.gz this Elektra version] 10:42, 29 Apr 2008 (CEST)


First check out:
 $ git clone git://www.oyranos.org/git/oyranos

The Oyranos included ICC profiles are not included in git. Take them from [http://downloads.sourceforge.net/oyranos/oyranos-0.1.8.tar.gz oyranos-0.1.8.tar.gz] and move the standard_profiles directory into the cloned git directory.

Building Oyranos:
 $ cd oyranos/
 $ configure
 $ make
 $ make install

Keeping Oyranos up to date:
 $ git pull

Examining the history:
 $ git log -p

A script to automate the process, including a build of [[ICC Examin]], is [https://www.behrmann.name/temp/icc_examin-build.sh here].
The script accepts options for configure and will pass them unchanged. 

E.g. --prefix=/my/reachable/path might be a good idea to avoid the requirement root rights for installation of a test build.

ICC Examin git can be obtained without the above script like follows:
 $ git clone git://www.oyranos.org/git/icc_examin

